<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-17T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-17T15:00:00-05:00" n="1150" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1150">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Italy)/2–1345:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-17T16:00:00-04:00">February
                                    17, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>331. Department appreciates information contained in your 388 February 13
                            and your analysis of financial proposals. Your comments appear to us to
                            deserve fundamental review of our financial proposals. Would you object
                            to our giving this telegram to Treasury, and possibly War, for limited
                            distribution for purposes of such discussion?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>